Tip of the Day: How to Practice SQL and PySpark Effectively
There are many online platforms available to practice SQL and PySpark. However, most of these tools do not behave like a tutor. A good tutor doesn’t just provide questions—it asks you questions, evaluates your answers, identifies mistakes, and tells you what is missing or incorrect.
This is where ChatGPT can be a very effective learning tool.
You can use ChatGPT as an interactive tutor by simply giving it the right prompt. It will ask questions one at a time, analyze your answers, and provide detailed feedback—very similar to a real interview or mentor.
For Simple SQL Practice
Use this prompt:
Could you help me practice SQL? Ask one question at a time.
For Advanced SQL Practice
Use this prompt:
Could you help me practice advanced SQL? Ask one question at a time.
ChatGPT will:
Ask you a question
Analyze your response
Point out mistakes
Highlight what is missing or can be improved
This approach is extremely useful because in interviews, even a small mistake can lead to rejection. Practicing with a tool that helps you identify gaps in your answers can significantly improve accuracy and confidence.
 
